  <Docs>
    <summary>PagerTitleStrip is a non-interactive indicator of the current, next,
 and previous pages of a <c><see cref="T:Android.Support.V4.View.ViewPager" /></c>.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">PagerTitleStrip is a non-interactive indicator of the current, next,
 and previous pages of a <c><see cref="T:Android.Support.V4.View.ViewPager" /></c>. It is intended to be used as a
 child view of a ViewPager widget in your XML layout.
 Add it as a child of a ViewPager in your layout file and set its
 android:layout_gravity to TOP or BOTTOM to pin it to the top or bottom
 of the ViewPager. The title from each page is supplied by the method
 <c><see cref="M:Android.Support.V4.View.PagerAdapter.GetPageTitleFormatted(System.Int32)" /></c> in the adapter supplied to
 the ViewPager.

 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">For an interactive indicator, see <c><see cref="T:Android.Support.V4.View.PagerTabStrip" /></c>.</para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/android/support/v4/view/PagerTitleStrip.html" target="_blank">[Android Documentation]</a>
        </format>
      </para>
    </remarks>
    <since version="" />
